author: WCAX News
title: Police ID Morristown crash victim
text:
MORRISTOWN, Vt. - Police have identified the man who was killed in a crash in Morristown Thursday.
The three-car crash happened on Route 100 at about 6:15 a.m. Police say a pickup truck headed south crossed the center line, sideswiped one car, and then collided head-on with a second car.
The driver of the pickup, Justin Delabruere, 31, of Island Pond, was killed in the crash.
The driver of the second car, Erica Ciaraldi, 41, of Stowe, was seriously injured in the collision. The driver of the other car was not injured.
Police are still investigating the cause of the crash and would like to hear from anyone who witnessed it. Call Morristown Police at 802-888-4211.
